<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Minority To Take Part in Census </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Minority To Take Part in Census </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005174794 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3005174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Serbs Will Take Part in Census, </F>
Perhaps Not in Elections"] 
  [Text] At a press conference, the Democratic Association 
of Serbs stated the Serbs in Macedonia [Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia] are ready to cooperate in realization of the 
coming census and will take part in it. The Association 
President Boro Ristic pointed out the census is a test for the 
democracy and statehood of Macedonia. He appealed to all Serbs 
in Macedonia to declare themselves Serbs, and not Yugoslavs. 
  As for the elections laws, the Association suggests the 
parliament should consist of 120 deputies elected on a majority 
principle, 15 on a proportional one, and five deputies, to be 
appointed by the Ethnic Council. "Unless the parliament accepts 
this proposal or comes up with an adequate coalition partner to 
protect the rights of Serbs in Macedonia, the Association will 
boycott the elections in November," Ristic stated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

