<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Party Protests Census Structure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Party Protests Census Structure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005174694 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3005174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Parallel Census?"] </F>
  [Text] The Democratic Party of Turks in Macedonia [Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia] expressed bitterness and public 
protest against the structure of the State Census Committee, 
appointed by the government. The Turk member of the Committee 
has been appointed without consulting the party, which is for 
them unacceptable. The party is confirmed the census will be 
conducted in a manner same as all previous censuses, i.e., it 
will be partial and doubtful. If this party is neglected in the 
future, it will announce a parallel census for Turks in 
Macedonia to be conducted by Turks, the party threatened in its 
public announcement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

