<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Propose Amendment to Constitution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Propose Amendment to Constitution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   11111111 </F>
<F P=103> 11111111 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106>   [Unattributed report: "Constitutional Proposal Changes"] </F>
  [Text] The Macedonian Council on Ethnic Relations held a 
session, discussing amendments to the Constitution, proposed by 
its member Bosko Despotic, representative of the Serbs and 
Montenegrins in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia]. The Coordinating Committee of the Association of 
Serbs and Montenegrins in Macedonia submitted a request for 
changes in the constitution, to state Serbs, not mentioning 
Montenegrins, along with other minorities living in Macedonia. 
The second amendment proposes equal participation of Serbs in 
the work of the Ethnic Council. 
  The Council is to decide on the proposed amendments during 
one of its next sessions. 

</TEXT>

