<H3> <TI>   Local Official Claims Villages of Greek Origin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Local Official Claims Villages of Greek Origin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705161594 Tirana ATA in English 1218 GMT 27 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2705161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["A Document Which Testifies to the Involvement of </F>
Janullatos Subordinates in the Anti-Albanian Policy" -- ATA 
headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, May 27 (ATA) -- The chairman of the 
Managing Council of Saranda Religious Commission, Mr. Niko 
Papanikolau, has issued a document in Greek language, which 
serves as a legal document in Greece, for an Albanian citizen 
from a village near Vlore. On the document is written "Villages 
Narte and Zvernec of Vlore are Greek villages and their 
inhabitants are of Greek origin, speak Greek language, and 
belong to Orthodox religion. 
  In the document is also written "Albanian state has 
registered as Albanian citizens the people of Narte and Zvernec 
villages, the same thing has happened with Himare region. 
  Saranda Council, Omonia, and Sillogu of northern Epirus in 
Corfu are the three institutions of Greek state, which are 
authorized to issue different certificates for the Albanians of 
southern part of the country, reports newspaper REPUBLIKA on May 
26. 

</TEXT>

