<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Slovak National Bank Renewed Refinancing"] </F>
  [Text] In the 22d week, after a period of approximately 
three months, the Slovak National Bank [NBS] again started to 
refinance commercial banks by means of auction credits. Even 
earlier, the NBS renewed the rediscount of exchange bills for 
agriculture. According to information from the NBS, the above 
measures can be regarded as an indication of good marcoeconomic 
results, such as, for example, the favorable development of the 
inflation rate, which reached only three percent in the first 
four months of this year. 

