<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Progress in Dismantling Military Gear Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Progress in Dismantling Military Gear Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705160794 Prague RUDE PRAVO in Czech 23 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2705160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague RUDE PRAVO </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["(per)"-signed report: "Another 417 Tanks Still Have To Be </F>
Destroyed"] 
  [Text] Prague -- The Czech Army has 417 surplus tanks, 43 
armored vehicles, 52 artillery, and 38 combat aircraft to 
dismantle before 15 November 1995. The dismantlement, which is 
taking place on the basis of the Treaty on Conventional Armed 
Forces in Europe, has already cost the Czech Army 60 million 
korunas. The Federal Army committed itself to dismantle 1,880 
tanks, 2,450 armored personnel carriers, 2,303 artillery, and 98 
combat aircraft. The dismantlement of the surplus hardware has 
been carried out in the military repair shops in Novy Jicin, 
Sternberk, Jaromer, Terezin, Vodochody, and Prerov. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-30958 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu106_i_94002" </HT>


