<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic Gives Conditions for Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Izetbegovic Gives Conditions for Peace Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0106183994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0106183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Presidency of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, today received Vitaliy Churkin, special 
envoy to the Russian president for Bosnia-Herzegovina. The 
talks were attended by Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic. Churkin 
expressed interest in Bosnia-Herzegovina's stands regarding the 
cease-fire with the Serbian aggressor and the possible 
participation of a Bosnia-Herzegovina delegation at the 
negotiations on the political solution to the crisis. 
  Izetbegovic informed Churkin of the positions he had also 
presented to the Assembly of Bosnia-Herzegovina. The Russian 
envoy said that he expected Serbs to withdraw from the Gorazde 
protected zone, something that Izetbegovic had set as a 
condition for negotiations to continue. The Bosnian side has no 
objections to the Serbian population remaining in the Gorazde 
region, but only if the people involved are those who had lived 
on the said territory before the war. It is known that the 
Serbian aggressor forces are trying to colonize the Gorazde 
region, which was also pointed out to [words indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

