<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Signs PHARE Project Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0206074994 Tirana ATA in English 1034 GMT 1 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0206074994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 1 (ATA) -- The agreement on the 
PHARE-94 [Economic and Reconstruction Aid for Poland and 
Hungary] project for Albania was signed May 31 at the Ministry 
of Finance. "This ceremony left me a very strong impression," 
said Elio Germano, ambassador of the European Union in Tirana. 
With the signing of this agreement, he said, we confirmed that 
the European Union will stand side by side Albania to help it 
with the developing processes and the economic and institutional 
reform. The signing of this document implies that Albania 
should be increasingly close to a decentralised economy and 
programs projected for the Albanian people, Mr. Germano said. 
"During our stay in Albania, we have worked to conclude this 
program as soon as possible and completely, something which also 
serves the strengthening of our relations," he concluded. 

</TEXT>

