<H3> <TI>   Mining Cooperation Agreement Signed With China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mining Cooperation Agreement Signed With China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106194494 Warsaw PAP in English 1745 GMT 1 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0106194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Katowice, June 1 -- Deputy Industry and Trade 
Minister Herbert Gabrys and Deputy Minister of the Coal Industry 
of The People's Republic of China Zhang Baoming on Wednesday 
signed an agreement on the resumption of the activity of the 
permanent interministerial working team for the coal industry. 
  In the "Staszic" colliery, head of the coal company in 
Pingdingshan, Liang Youping, head of the "Katowice Coal Holding 
SA" Tadeusz Demel and colliery director Miroslaw Major signed an 
agreement on cooperation. 
  The Chinese deputy minister said a reform is underway in the 
Chinese coal mining industry, which aims at adjusting this 
sector to the market requirements in management, progress in 
science and technology and modern know-how. 
  The Staszic director said the Chinese coal industry 
delegation toured the colliery and watched the work of the 
Polish-manufactured machines which allow to increase tenfold 
hard coal extraction from one longwall. The Chinese guests were 
also interested in the organisational structure of the colliery, 
its financial results, the winding gear and the work of the mine 
rescue service station. 

</TEXT>

