<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 31/5/1994 -- Indian President 
Shankar Dayal Sharma, now on an official visit to Romania, 
addressed the two chambers of Romania's Parliament in joint 
sitting on 31 May. 
  The Indian president conveyed to Romania "the fraternal 
salute of India's Government, Parliament and people." He spoke 
of freedom and democracy and showed that where there was freedom 
of thought and expression the most differing views could be set 
forth, to the benefit of democracy. 
  The visit by the Indian president, who is accompanied by a 
delegation of ministers and parliamentarians, is the first visit 
after 1989 by an Asian head of state to Romania. 
  Romanian Senate President Oliviu Gherman assessed in his 
welcoming address that India was a potential supporter of the 
development of Romania's relations with other Asian states. He 
also hoped Romania would be able to be in turn a European gate 
for India. 

</TEXT>

