1300 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After a long period of truce, the Serbs launched 
another artillery attacks on Mostar. Ankica Posavljak has a 
report: 
  [Posavljak] The information center of Mostar reports that a 
general alert was sounded at 1259 in the town. We were informed 
by the Information and Political Service of the Croatian Defense 
Council for the Mostar operational area that 10 tank shells were 
fired from Serbian positions located at the foot of Mt. Velez. 
The Mostar suburbs of Cim, Orlovac, Ilici, and Zovnica in the 
western part of Mostar, which are under Croatian Defense Council 
control, were targeted. 
  A base of the Spanish UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] 
battalion in Mostar was also hit and several vehicles were 
damaged. There have been no reports of casualties, but 
considerable material damage has been caused. 

