<H3> <TI>   Serbian Attacks on Gracanica Intensify </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Attacks on Gracanica Intensify </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306090394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0306090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hasan Galic from Gracanica] </F>
  [Text] In the course of the night and early this morning 
the Chetniks have continued attacking in the zone of 
responsibility of the Gracanica Operative Group [words 
indistinct] 109th Doboj Brigade. The infantry attacks were 
accompanied by the shelling of our defense lines and suburban 
settlements (?Glokotici), (?Prisic), Lukavica, and 
(Lukavica-Rijeka). The chetniks were particularly active 
between 2000 and 2200 hours when over 200 projectiles of various 
calibers landed on our lines and the aforementioned civilian 
settlements. This was followed by a ferocious infantry attack. 
By resisting successfully this attack, our fighters have 
liquidated a great number of Chetniks, who were left between the 
lines and are still lying there, which says enough about the 
enemy's attitude toward their dead soldiers. 
  The late night saw a concentration of the Serbian forces and 
sporadic shelling. However, as of 0400 this morning the attacks 
have intensified. 
  The aim of these enemy attacks is to gain control over 
important elevations (?Pribevine), Oblic, and Banjic in order to 
widen the security ring around Doboj. As of 0900 a general 
alarm has been in force in Gracanica. 

</TEXT>

