<H3> <TI>   Muslim Infighting Continues in Western Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Infighting Continues in Western Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306115694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1059 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0306115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Petrovac, June 3 (TANJUG) -- A member of the forces 
of the autonomous province of western Bosnia was killed Thursday 
[2 June] in attacks by forces loyal to Bosnian Muslim leader 
Alija Izetbegovic, local Muslim media reported. According to 
Radio Velkaton in Velika Kladusa, the capital of the province, 
the heaviest fighting was reported in the Liskovac region and 
the forces of the autonomous province tried to prevent 
Izetbegovic's forces from penetrating their defense lines. 
  The same source says that Izetbegovic forces continued with 
heavy shelling of Pecigrad. Muslims in the western part of the 
former republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina declared their autonomy 
last September standing up against the war-mongering policy of 
Izetbegovic and disassociating themselves from the decisions of 
the Muslim leadership in Sarajevo. 
  Since then, Western Bosnia-Herzegovina has been the scene of 
fierce intra-Muslim clashes, where Izetbegovic has sent his 
troops against his countrymen instructing them to stifle the new 
autonomy `with all available means'. 

</TEXT>

