<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Civic Council Proposes Assembly Debate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Civic Council Proposes Assembly Debate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306115494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0306115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a letter addressed to the chairman of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly Miro Lazovic, the Serbian Civic 
Council proposed that the next session of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Assembly includes a debate about the strategy toward the Serbian 
question and the constitutional position of the citizens of 
Serbian ethnicity on the territory of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Federation. 
  The Serbian Civic Council proposes that the amendment to the 
constitution of the federation that was proposed at the last 
session of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly forms the basis for 
the debate at the next session of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Assembly. The Serbian Civic Council believes that Legislation 
Minister Kasim Trnka, one of the authors of the Constitution of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Federation, and one representative of the 
Serbian Civic Council should speak about the position of the 
Serbs within the federation. It would be imperative to obtain 
the views and opinions of the constitutional commission of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly and Government prior to the assembly 
session, is stated in a letter of the Serbian Civic Council to 
Miro Lazovic. 

</TEXT>

