<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akashi Says Serbs Resuming Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Akashi Says Serbs Resuming Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0306101494 Paris AFP in English 0952 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0306101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, June 3 (AFP) -- Serb forces resumed Friday 
their withdrawal from the UN-declared exclusion zone around 
Gorazde in eastern Bosnia, raising hopes that truce talks 
stalled since Thursday would be able to get under way, UN 
special envoy Yasushi Akashi said Friday. Speaking after a 
meeting with Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, Akashi said 
he hoped the Geneva talks, aimed at securing an overall 
ceasefire in Bosnia-Herzegovina, could start on Saturday morning. 

</TEXT>

