<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meetings, Talks on Bosnia Continue in Geneva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meetings, Talks on Bosnia Continue in Geneva </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs Walk Out of Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD0506115494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1128 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0506115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, 5 Jun (TANJUG) -- The delegation of the 
Srpska Republic left the Palais des Nations in Geneva after 
several postponements of the talks on a cease-fire in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Srpska republic president Radovan Karadzic 
refused to say whether the delegation would return. 
  Earlier at a press conference Karadzic accused the Muslims 
of 
continually sabotaging the conference. "This is a great 
humiliation for the international community which bears the 
responsibility for these actions. Before the negotiations we 
were asked not to set any conditions, and we stuck to that. On 
the other hand, we are witnessing constant blackmail by the 
Muslims. There will be no peace without a cease-fire," Karadzic 
said and left the Palais des Nations with his delegation. 

</TEXT>

