<F P=106> [CTK report: "Counterintelligence Has a New Director"] </F>
  [Text] Prague--Defense Minister Antonin Baudys yesterday 
appointed Jiri Ruzek (1952) to the post of director of the 
Military Defense Intelligence Main Office. Until now, he had 
been deputy director of the Interior Ministry's Office for 
Foreign Relations and Information, which replaced our 
intelligence service abroad. However, according to Interior 
Ministry representatives, it does not conduct traditional 
espionage, and its staff apparently is working officially at our 
embassies. 

</TEXT>

