<H3> <TI>   MSZP To Seek Coalition With SZDSZ </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSZP To Seek Coalition With SZDSZ </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406152894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1500 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gyula Horn has become the MSZP [Hungarian Socialist 
Party] candidate for the post of prime minister. At the 
emergency congress which has just ended 431 delegates voted for 
him out of the 450. 
  The delegates also decided unanimously that they will ask 
the 
SZDSZ [Alliance of Free Democrats] to become the MSZP coalition 
partner. They have already sent the letter outlining this to 
Ivan Petoe, chairman of the SZDSZ. In the letter the MSZP 
emphasizes that the interest of the country would be served by a 
joint government by the two parties. The Socialists are ready 
for a compromise in every essential issue, the letter states. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

