  [Excerpts] The presidium of the Hungarian Socialist Party 
[MSZP] proposes [Chairman] Gyula Horn for prime minister. The 
closed session of the party presidium, which ended not long ago, 
will be followed by a meeting of the national executive and 
tomorrow's congress, at which the final decision will be made on 
the nomination of the prime minister. Kata Peli Nagy interviewed 
Imre Szekeres, the party's executive deputy chairman. 
