<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   FYROM Assembly President Meets Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FYROM Assembly President Meets Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206180294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1601 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 2 Jun (TANJUG) -- Stojan Andov, president of 
the Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- 
FYROM] assembly, arrived in Tirana today on a two-day official 
and friendly visit to Albania, Radio Skopje reported from the 
Albanian capital. This morning Andov held talks for one hour 
with Pjeter Arbnori, president of the Albanian assembly. They 
exchanged views on the cooperation between the two assemblies 
and states and on the situation in the Balkans. 
  Arbnori said that Macedonia and Albania "cooperate well in 
many domains," and that "they are very good neighbors." The 
cooperation would be even better if the Albanians in Macedonia 
were granted "all rights," Arbnori said. 
  Andov said that there were "many problems" between the two 
states, but, he stressed, "a way of solving them has been 
found." According to him, the problems connected with the rights 
of the Albanians in Macedonia are dealt with in the institutions 
of the system in line with the highest European standards on 
minority rights, or even better. He expressed the hope that the 
Macedonians in Albania would be granted the same rights and 
freedoms. 
  The president of the assembly of the Former Yugoslav 
Republic 
of Macedonia today also had a meeting with Albanian President 
Sali Berisha. Berisha said that he expected this visit to 
contribute to the further development of cooperation between the 
two countries and that he was happy that what he had agreed on 
with President Gligorov during their meeting last month in 
Pogradec was being realized. The Albanian president welcomed 
the adoption of the law on the population census in Macedonia 
and noted the need to develop traffic links between the two 
countries, including the links with the port of Durres, which 
should serve the Macedonian economy as well. 
  During the talks, Berisha also mentioned the position of the 
Albanian minority in Kosovo-Metohija and spoke against forcible 
changes to the border. Berisha thanked Gligorov for his 
invitation to visit Macedonia and announced his visit to Skopje 
in the near future. 
  During his talks with Berisha, Andov said that "essential 
steps forward have been taken" in the cooperation between 
Macedonia and Albania and that "there are no obstacles to the 
development and strengthening of cooperation." According to 
Andov, Macedonia and Albania are "linked in terms of their fate 
and oriented toward one other." 

</TEXT>

