<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Plan `Execution' of Captured Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Plan `Execution' of Captured Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606110794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1034 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zvornik, June 6 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Moslems have 
prepared a plan for the execution of Serbs captured in the area 
of Mt. Ozren in northeastern Bosnia, Bosnian Serb sources have 
told TANJUG. 
  The Bosnian Serb humanitarian aid organisation has apprised 
the International Committee of the Red cross (I.C.R.C.) office 
in Bijeljina about the planned execution of the Serbs captured 
on Mt. Ozren, and appealed to the I.C.R.C. officials to take the 
necessary steps to save the captives' lives. 
  In a letter to the I.C.R.C. office, the Serb humanitarian 
organisation says that Moslem extremists have brutally murdered 
and then mutilated the bodies of large numbers of captured Serbs 
in the course of this war, especially in the areas of Fakovici, 
Kamenica, Kravica near Milic, Brcko and elsewhere in eastern 
Bosnia. 
  In mid-1992, Moslem troops stormed and torched 43 Serb 
villages in eastern Bosnia, massacring 960 Serb civilians, 
mostly old men, women and children. 
  Serbs who have fled Tuzla with Croat help for 
Serb-controlled 
territories testify that the position of their ethnic kin in 
Tuzla is worsening, with the town's Moslem authorities evicting 
them from their homes and taking them away in an unknown 
direction. 
  In fear of their lives, Serbs in Tuzla are taking shelter 
with Croat families in the area, witnesses say. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

