<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Attacking North of Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Attacking North of Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0606101594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0606101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by the 3d Corps Press Center] </F>
  [Text] The chetniks are attacking the free Zavidovici 
territories with all means and (?manpower). They started by 
firing infantry and antiaircraft weapons at the defense lines, 
then they attacked (?Boscelovo), Bozici, (Lazanici), and [name 
indistinct] Bukva more fiercely. They have fired more than 30 
mortar bombs at Hajderevici from (Sunici) and 15 shells at 
Smailbasici from (Paljenici). (?Four) mortar [word indistinct] 
have been constantly pounding the villages of Bresevine and 
Tolici. A sniper is active at (Zebni Vrh). There are motor 
vehicle movements on the (Sok-Vodjuca) line all the time. 
  Throughout the day yesterday, the aggressor's infantry and 
antiaircraft weapons were active on the Doboj-Tesanj and Teslic- 
[word indistinct] and from time to time mortars could be heard. 
(?Any) infantry breakthrough attempt at the 3d Corps defense 
lines was prevented with great losses being inflicted on the 
chetnik ranks. 
  Several subversive groups that had been dispatched were 
completely crushed. 

</TEXT>

