<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Use New Kinds of Weapons on Brcko Front </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Use New Kinds of Weapons on Brcko Front </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506192794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0506192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Enemy forces fired on the central part of the 
Brcko defense and the defenders' positions in [name indistinct]. 
[passage omitted] 
  The aggressor is increasingly using new kinds of weapons. 
Today large numbers of projectiles 70 mm in diameter and 128-mm 
long were fired from Serb positions in Lipovac on Klade, using 
drum-shaped launchers installed on transporters. These weapons 
are manufactured in Russia. The highly destructive projectiles 
have built-in time fuses. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

