<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Attacks Against Serb Positions Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Attacks Against Serb Positions Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606104994 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1025 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Zvornik, June 6 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Moslems on 
Monday continued their armed operations against the Bosnian Serb 
Republic, in what the Serb Army sees as an obvious attempt to 
jeopardize the convention and outcome of Geneva peace talks. 
  There are no armed Serbs within the 3-km exclusion zone 
around Gorazde, the Moslem enclave in eastern Bosnia, which the 
U.N. Protection Force (UNPROFOR) has also confirmed, Bosnian 
Serb Army sources inform. The Moslems are continuing also to 
violate the ceasefire in the Sarajevo area, attacking from small 
arms the Serb localities of Ilijas, Vogosca, Ilidza, Nedjarici 
and Kasindol Street. 
  On the Ozren front, the Moslems mounted a combined artillery 
and infantry attack on the Serb defence positions on the 
southern slopes of Mt Ozren and in the Srbobran and Komar areas 
in the northeast, TANJUG learns. 
  The Bosnian Croat Army and the army of neighbouring Croatia 
are engaged in provocations along most of the lines of 
separation with Bosnia's Serbs on the Orasje front in the north. 
  Moslem operations against the Serbs are still going strong 
in 
the areas of Doboj, Teslic, Treabava and Vlasic in central 
Bosnia, and the Bihac and Krupa areas in the west. Moslems are 
provoking the Serbs also in the Sava River valley, especially 
around Brcko, which is situated in the neck of a vital corridor 
which links the east and west of the Bosnian Serb Republic, Serb 
Army sources say. 

</TEXT>

